lead_paragraph: The House leader in Florida sent members home over an impasse with the Senate — both chambers are controlled by Republicans — about expanding the federal government’s program to provide medical care to the poor.

headline.print_headline: Florida’s House Adjourns Early in Quarrel With Senate Over Medicaid
headline.main: Florida’s House Adjourns Early in Quarrel With Senate Over Medicaid

snippet: The House leader in Florida sent members home over an impasse with the Senate — both chambers are controlled by Republicans — about expanding the federal government’s program to provide medical care to the poor.
abstract: Florida Legislature adjourns three days early as battle over Medicaid expansion turns bitter, bringing debate over state's $77 billion budget, along with number of unfinished bills, to an unexpected halt; House speaker and Senate president, both Republicans, must now agree to a special session in order for Legislature to resume.
